    "title": [
      "[Olbin Strath, Farm]"
    ],
    "description": [
      "Framed by hardy apple trees that sag under a weight of unharvested fruit, a dirt path leads up to an old painted modwir farmhouse.  Staring accusatorily down at the yard, a broken window looks into a bedroom on the top floor.  The quiet is a palpable thing, as if bird and beast and even the wind shun the place.  Even so, the door creaks now and then on rusty hinges."
    ],
